JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Gem Diamonds has recovered a 114 ct, D colour type II diamond of exceptional quality from its Let&scaron;eng mine, in Lesotho. The Let&scaron;eng mine is known for producing large, top colour, exceptional white diamonds, making it the highest dollar-per-carat kimberlite diamond mine in the world. Since Gem Diamonds&#39; acquisition of Let&scaron;eng in 2006, the mine has produced four of the 20 largest gem-quality white diamonds ever recorded.